WEBVTT

00:01.340 --> 00:02.546
- HEY, HONEY,
DID YOU FIND THE DIAPER BAG YET?

00:02.650 --> 00:03.332
- NO,
I DIDN'T FIND IT.

00:03.450 --> 00:04.712
I PACKED IT
EARLIER THIS MORNING.

00:04.830 --> 00:06.058
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO IT.

00:06.170 --> 00:07.307
- WELL, LISTEN, HONEY,
WE'RE NOT GOING TO GET

00:07.420 --> 00:08.102
VERY FAR ON THIS ROAD TRIP
WITHOUT A DIAPER BAG, OKAY?

00:08.210 --> 00:09.347
- I AGREE.
- SO LET'S FIND IT.

00:09.450 --> 00:11.270
- MAX, HONEY, CAN YOU PLEASE
TURN THAT DOWN FOR MOM?

00:11.390 --> 00:12.618
IT'S SO LOUD.
DID HE PACK HIS BAG?

00:12.730 --> 00:15.244
- MAX, VOLUME. UH, I DON'T KNOW.
MAX, DID YOU PACK YOUR BAG?

00:15.360 --> 00:16.736
- I HATE THE WEEK
AFTER THE HOLIDAYS.

00:16.840 --> 00:18.455
THERE'S SO MUCH CHAOS.
THERE'S NO STRUCTURE.

00:18.570 --> 00:19.355
THERE'S CANDY EVERYWHERE.
THERE'S TOYS AROUND--

00:19.460 --> 00:21.564
MAX, PLEASE!
PLEASE, I'M BEGGING YOU.

00:21.670 --> 00:23.080
- HONEY, DID YOU LOOK
IN THE KITCHEN?

00:23.190 --> 00:25.112
- IT'S NOT IN THE KITCHEN,
OKAY?

00:25.230 --> 00:26.219
WHY WOULD I PUT IT
IN THE KITCHEN?

00:26.330 --> 00:27.251
SO WHAT? THERE'S NO--
- OH, GOD!

00:27.370 --> 00:28.257
- OW!
- SORRY, OOH!

00:28.370 --> 00:29.598
- ADAM, YOU KNOW WHAT?
- HONEY, LISTEN.

00:29.710 --> 00:32.122
YOU SEEM A LITTLE OVERWHELMED.
CAN YOU JUST TAKE A BREATH?

00:32.230 --> 00:33.401
ALL RIGHT, I'M SORRY.
SORRY.

00:33.510 --> 00:35.239
- I AM A LITTLE BIT
OVERWHELMED.

00:35.340 --> 00:36.329
WHY WOULD YOUR DAD PLAN THIS
TRIP TO GO SEE YOUR GRANDMOTHER?

00:36.450 --> 00:38.406
HE DOESN'T EVEN LIKE HIS MOTHER.
- IT'S HER BIRTHDAY.

00:38.520 --> 00:39.828
HEY,
THAT'S A LITTLE HARSH, OKAY?

00:39.930 --> 00:41.272
EVERYBODY LOVES THEIR MOTHER.
I'M GONNA LOOK IN THE KITCHEN.

00:41.380 --> 00:43.245
- HE DOESN'T LIKE
HIS MOTHER.

00:43.350 --> 00:45.409
[loud grunting on TV]
MAX!

00:45.520 --> 00:46.999
[baby crying]

00:47.110 --> 00:49.999
[Shirley Ellis'
The Nitty Gritty]

00:50.110 --> 00:51.520
- SOME WILL LEARN
TO SHOUT IT

00:51.630 --> 00:53.313
SOME WON'T

00:53.430 --> 00:55.705
BUT SOONER OR LATER, BABY,
HERE'S A DI'I'I'Y

00:55.810 --> 00:57.118
- OH, MY GOSH!

00:57.220 --> 00:59.290
THAT FEELS SO GOOD.

00:59.400 --> 01:00.606
- YES!

01:00.710 --> 01:02.086
OH, OH!
- SEE?

01:02.200 --> 01:03.155
[laughter]

01:03.270 --> 01:05.329
- YES, YES, YES.
- ALL RIGHT, OKAY, OKAY.

01:05.440 --> 01:06.293
- WE'RE SAYING NOW
THAT I HAVE 24 HOURS

01:06.410 --> 01:08.230
TO GET THIS BRIEF WRITTEN?

01:08.340 --> 01:10.262
NO, NO, NO, NO, I-I WILL DO IT.
I WILL DO IT.

01:10.380 --> 01:11.233
I'M JUST GOING
OUT OF TOWN,

01:11.340 --> 01:12.750
SO I'LL HAVE TO DO IT
ON THE ROAD.

01:12.860 --> 01:14.475
OKAY, THANK YOU.
THAT'S FINE, BYE.

01:14.590 --> 01:16.797
- YOU SURE
WE'RE NOT UNDERPACKED?

01:16.900 --> 01:19.209
- [scoffs]
- YOUR DAD CALLED AGAIN.

01:19.320 --> 01:20.344
- YEAH.
- HE WANTS US ON THE ROAD

01:20.450 --> 01:22.520
AT 0900 THIS MORNING,
ON THE DOT.

01:22.630 --> 01:26.418
- SWEETIE, IT'S TIME TO GO.
ARE YOU READY?

01:26.530 --> 01:29.385
HE FREAKS OUT ABOUT GRANDMA.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS.

01:29.500 --> 01:32.424
- BUT IT'S RIGHT THERE.
YOU CAN'T JUST GRAB IT?

01:32.540 --> 01:34.292
- MAX, HONEY, IT'S TIME
TO WRAP IT UP, LET'S GO.

01:34.400 --> 01:36.322
- THERE.
- I'M ALMOST DONE.

01:36.440 --> 01:38.431
- NO, YOU'RE DONE NOW.
MAX?

01:38.540 --> 01:39.711
[grunting]

01:39.820 --> 01:42.402
MAX.

01:42.510 --> 01:44.193
MAX, WE'RE LEAVING.
- I SAID, "I'M ALMOST DONE."

01:44.310 --> 01:46.710
[grunting on TV continues]

01:46.830 --> 01:49.207
FIVE MORE.

01:49.310 --> 01:51.175
ONE MORE.
WAIT.

01:51.280 --> 01:52.554
NO!
- WE'RE DONE.

01:52.660 --> 01:54.582
- DO YOU REALIZE
WHAT YOU JUST DID?

01:54.700 --> 01:55.689
- DON'T YELL AT ME.

01:55.800 --> 01:57.791
- I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON THAT LEVEL FOR DAYS.

01:57.910 --> 01:59.218
- STOP YELLING.
- DAYS!

01:59.320 --> 02:00.799
I JUST LOST EVERYTHING!

02:00.910 --> 02:02.252
- STOP IT.
IT DOESN'T MA'I'I'ER.

02:02.360 --> 02:03.384
I'VE BEEN TELLING YOU
FOR THE PAST HOUR

02:03.500 --> 02:05.661
TO TURN IT OFF, AND YOU'VE
NOT LISTENED TO ME ONCE.

02:05.780 --> 02:09.159
- YOU'RE SUCH A BITCH!
- DO NOT TH--

02:09.260 --> 02:11.364
WHAT DID YOU JUST SAY TO ME?
- YOU'RE SUCH A BITCH!

02:11.470 --> 02:14.291
- OKAY,
THAT IS IT!

02:14.410 --> 02:16.093
YOU ARE BEING PUNISHED!
YOU'RE PUNISHED.

02:16.200 --> 02:17.406
- OH, YEAH, RIGHT.
- YOU'RE--

02:17.510 --> 02:19.398
- LIKE LAST SATURDAY, WHEN YOU
SAID I WOULDN'T BE ABLE

02:19.510 --> 02:20.442
TO GO TO THE MOVIES,
AND THEN YOU TOTALLY FORGOT...

02:20.550 --> 02:21.517
- THAT IS--
- AND WE ENDED UP GOING ANYWAY?

02:21.620 --> 02:24.783
- I AM--YOU--
YOU'RE NOT GOING ON THIS TRIP.

02:24.900 --> 02:26.174
- WHAT?
- GET UPSTAIRS NOW!

02:26.280 --> 02:27.724
YOU'RE NOT GOING ON THIS TRIP.
THAT'S IT.

02:27.830 --> 02:30.003
- THIS IS SO UNFAIR!
- DON'T THROW STUFF AT ME.

02:30.110 --> 02:31.657
- I HATE YOU!
- I'LL SAY WHAT'S FAIR

02:31.770 --> 02:33.146
AND WHAT'S NOT FAIR.
I'M THE MOM.

02:33.250 --> 02:37.766
IT'S FAIR.

02:37.880 --> 02:39.188
[sighs]

02:41.640 --> 02:43.494
- [sighs]
COME ON, CAMILLE.

02:43.610 --> 02:45.817
CAN WE HURRY IT UP A LITTLE?
WE GOT A SCHEDULE HERE.

02:45.920 --> 02:48.639
[sighs]

02:48.750 --> 02:49.648
- YOU'RE PACING.

02:49.750 --> 02:54.266
- I'M NOT PACING.

02:54.380 --> 02:56.132
- [coffeepot clatters]
SWEETIE?

02:56.240 --> 02:57.446
- MM.

02:57.550 --> 02:59.472
- UM, BEFORE WE DRAG
YOUR ENTIRE FAMILY ON THIS TRIP,

02:59.590 --> 03:03.447
ARE YOU SURE THAT YOU WANT
TO GO THROUGH WITH THIS?

03:03.560 --> 03:05.073
- AW, COME ON.
IT'S MY MOM'S 86TH BIRTHDAY.

03:05.180 --> 03:06.340
HELL, YEAH,
I WANT TO GO THROUGH--

03:06.460 --> 03:10.351
- YEAH, I KNOW, BUT WE DIDN'T GO
TO HER 85TH BIRTHDAY...

03:10.460 --> 03:11.904
OR HER 84TH BIRTHDAY,

03:12.010 --> 03:14.353
OR HER 77TH BIRTHDAY,
OR HER--

03:14.470 --> 03:16.085
- WELL, I MEAN, COME ON.
I--SHE HAS A FALL,

03:16.190 --> 03:18.249
SHE HURTS HERSELF,
I DON'T KNOW.

03:18.370 --> 03:21.157
YOU KNOW,
I JUST THOUGHT, YOU KNOW--

03:21.270 --> 03:23.192
- YEAH, I--
YEAH, I KNOW.

03:23.300 --> 03:24.506
- LOOK, I--
I'M GOING TO GO

03:24.610 --> 03:28.262
CHECK THE TIRES ON THE TRUCK,
ALL RIGHT?

03:28.380 --> 03:30.132
- IT'LL BE FINE.

03:30.240 --> 03:33.277
[door opens and closes]

03:33.380 --> 03:35.723
- I FOUND THE DIAPER BAG--
OKAY, HE HAS TO GO.

03:35.830 --> 03:36.649
- HE'S NOT GOING.
- YOU HAVE TO GO.

03:36.760 --> 03:38.239
NORA HAS TO GO.
WE ALL HAVE TO GO.

03:38.350 --> 03:40.409
- I'M NOT GOING,
AND NORA'S DEFINITELY NOT GOING

03:40.530 --> 03:41.519
UNLESS, OF COURSE, YOU CAN
NURSE, WHICH I DON'T SEE--

03:41.630 --> 03:45.009
- ALL RIGHT, LISTEN TO ME.
I THINK THIS IS EXTREME.

03:45.120 --> 03:47.497
- YOUR SON CALLED ME
A BITCH.

03:47.600 --> 03:49.352
HE CALLED ME A BITCH TW--
TWICE.

03:49.470 --> 03:50.562
- I UNDERSTAND THAT,
AND I'M SORRY, OKAY?

03:50.670 --> 03:51.466
- IT'S NOT COOL.

03:51.570 --> 03:52.537
- I'M SURE
HE DIDN'T MEAN IT,

03:52.640 --> 03:54.084
AND I WANNA COME UP
WITH A SOLUTION HERE.

03:54.190 --> 03:55.703
- I DON'T CARE
IF HE MEANT IT OR NOT--

03:55.820 --> 03:57.538
- WELL, WHY, OF ALL PUNISHMENTS,
DID YOU CHOOSE THIS?

03:57.650 --> 03:59.368
- BECAUSE IT JUST CAME OUT
OF MY MOUTH, OKAY?

03:59.480 --> 04:00.299
I NEED TO FOLLOW
THROUGH ON THIS.

04:00.410 --> 04:01.229
- WELL, CAN WE THINK
CREATIVELY?

04:01.340 --> 04:02.193
COME UP WITH A DIFFERENT
PUNISHMENT?

04:02.310 --> 04:03.163
- CREATIVELY WHAT?

04:03.270 --> 04:04.237
- MAYBE JUST ISSUE HIM
A WARNING?

04:04.340 --> 04:05.261
THIS IS SO IMPORTANT
TO MY DAD.

04:05.380 --> 04:06.062
- HIS HAPPINESS
IS MORE IMPORTANT THAN ME

04:06.170 --> 04:08.092
FOLLOWING THROUGH
ON A PUNISHMENT?

04:08.210 --> 04:09.279
- THAT'S NOT WHAT I'M SAYING.
- WHAT ABOUT OUR FAMILY?

04:09.380 --> 04:11.587
I NEED TO STICK TO MY GUNS
ON THIS, OKAY?

04:11.690 --> 04:14.079
I WARN HIM ALL THE TIME,
AND IT'S MEANINGLESS.

04:14.180 --> 04:16.933
- [sighs]
I GET IT.

04:17.040 --> 04:19.622
JUST MY DAD'S
GONNA FREAK.

04:19.740 --> 04:21.139
- I MEAN, LOOK AT IT
THIS WAY.

04:21.260 --> 04:22.397
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE FUN
WITH HADDIE, RIGHT?

04:22.500 --> 04:26.186
SOME BONDING TIME?
- YEAH, BE KINDA NICE.

04:26.300 --> 04:27.915
- I'M REALLY SORRY,
HONEY.

04:28.020 --> 04:30.124
[metal adjuster clicking]

04:30.230 --> 04:32.050
- NOW, HOLD ON.
[clears throat]

04:32.160 --> 04:35.505
- BOY, MAKE SURE YOU STRAP THAT
THING DOWN GOOD AND TIGHT NOW.

04:35.620 --> 04:37.611
- WELL, I WANT IT TIGHT.
I WANT IT SOLID.

04:37.720 --> 04:39.449
I DON'T WANT ANYBODY
STEALING IT.

04:39.550 --> 04:40.642
- I DON'T THINK WE
ACTUALLY HAVE TO WORRY

04:40.760 --> 04:42.375
ABOUT THIS BEING STOLEN,
YOU KNOW?

04:42.480 --> 04:44.300
- YEAH,
LOVELY AS IT IS.

04:44.420 --> 04:46.411
[horn honks]

04:46.520 --> 04:47.691
- HEY, ADAM'S HERE!
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

04:47.800 --> 04:50.246
MILLIE, YEAH,
GET THE TALKIES AND THE MAPS.

04:50.350 --> 04:51.521
COME ON, EVERYBODY.
LET'S GO.

04:51.630 --> 04:53.382
JOEL, HEY, HEY, YEAH.
- HEY.

04:53.500 --> 04:55.456
- DREW.
- GOOD MORNING.

04:55.570 --> 04:57.140
- HEY.
- HEY, YOU GUYS. COME ON, G--

04:57.260 --> 04:58.875
WHERE'S THE BABY?
WHERE'S KRISTINA?

04:58.980 --> 05:01.392
- UH, THEY COULDN'T MAKE IT,
DAD, SORRY.

05:01.500 --> 05:03.741
- WHAT, ARE THEY SICK?

05:03.850 --> 05:05.647
- IT'S THE BLUE ONE--
- LET'S GO.

05:05.750 --> 05:08.674
- NO, UH, JUST--
MAX GOT INTO IT WITH KRISTINA.

05:08.790 --> 05:11.509
AND SHE FELT LIKE SHE NEEDED
TO GIVE HIM A PUNISHMENT,

05:11.620 --> 05:13.064
AND THAT'S GONNA BE
NOT GOING ON THE TRIP.

05:13.170 --> 05:14.398
- WELL, MAYBE I SHOULD CALL--
- BUT SHE'S GO'I'I'A STAY HOME

05:14.520 --> 05:15.544
WITH THE BABY TOO,
ALL RIGHT?

05:15.660 --> 05:17.343
- CAN I CALL?
- NO.

05:17.450 --> 05:19.793
- BUT, ADAM, IT'S MY MOM'S
86TH BIRTHDAY, YOU KNOW?

05:19.900 --> 05:21.720
- DAD, I KNOW IT IS, I KNOW.
- THAT'S A LITTLE INSANE HERE.

05:21.830 --> 05:23.479
ALL RIGHT?
- IT'S NOT INSANE, DAD.

05:23.590 --> 05:24.591
THIS IS WHAT WE HAVE TO DO
FOR MAX SOMETIMES.

05:24.700 --> 05:26.588
- MAYBE WE SHOULD STOP BY
ON THE WAY OUT OF HERE--

05:26.700 --> 05:27.735
- WE CAN'T REACH MAX
ABOUT HIS BEHAVIOR

05:27.840 --> 05:29.148
UNLESS THERE ARE
CONSEQUENCES, OKAY?

05:29.250 --> 05:30.353
SO IT HAS TO GO DOWN
THIS WAY.

05:30.460 --> 05:31.563
I'VE GOTI'A BE SUPPORTIVE OF HER,
ALL RIGHT?

05:31.670 --> 05:34.184
CAN YOU JUST RESPECT THAT,
PLEASE?

05:34.290 --> 05:35.257
- SEE, UM, THE WALKIES.
- RIGHT, OKAY.

05:35.360 --> 05:36.873
ONE OF THESE PER CAR.
THANK YOU, CAMILLE.

05:36.990 --> 05:38.127
- OKAY.

05:38.230 --> 05:39.458
- ALL RIGHT,
PLEASE DON'T LOSE THESE.

05:39.580 --> 05:40.956
- NEXT CAR.
- IT'D BE HARD TO.

05:41.060 --> 05:42.288
- I'M PASSENGER--NAVIGATOR.
- THE ROUTE OF TRAVEL

05:42.410 --> 05:44.332
IS HIGHLIGHTED IN YELLOW.

05:44.440 --> 05:47.238
THERE ARE MENUS
INCLUDED IN THE PACKET,

05:47.340 --> 05:50.138
'CAUSE WE'RE GONNA BE STOPPING
AT CINDY'S DINER FOR LUNCH.

05:50.240 --> 05:52.652
EXIT 127. SO EVERYBODY CAN FILL
OUT THEIR LI'ITLE ORDER FORM.

05:52.760 --> 05:55.240
[overlapping chatter]
WE DON'T HAVE TO WAIT AROUND

05:55.350 --> 05:57.693
FOR THAT 'CAUSE IT TAKES FOREVER
WITH THE LITTLE ONES, OKAY?

05:57.800 --> 06:00.667
- IS THIS LIKE A PAPER GPS?
- S--NOW, THE WALKIE-TALKIES.

06:00.770 --> 06:03.216
LET ME EXPLAIN SOMETHING.
- DO THEY STILL WORK?

06:03.320 --> 06:05.629
- L--THEY DO, AND LISTEN UP,
ALL RIGHT?

06:05.740 --> 06:09.460
THESE ARE MISSION-SPECIFIC USE
ONLY.

06:09.570 --> 06:11.083
- OKAY.
- THEY'RE NOT TOYS.

06:11.190 --> 06:11.849
DON'T FOOL AROUND WITH THEM.

06:11.950 --> 06:13.463
- CAN WE JUST USE
THE CELL PHONES...

06:13.580 --> 06:15.081
- NO.
- THAT WE ALL HAVE?

06:15.200 --> 06:16.189
- YOU CAN'T USE CELL PHONES

06:16.300 --> 06:17.335
WHILE YOU'RE DRIVING,
JOEL.

06:17.440 --> 06:19.362
- COME ON, JOEL.
- JOEL.

06:19.480 --> 06:22.369
- SORRY, IT'S A STUPID QUESTION,
GUYS.

06:22.480 --> 06:24.402
- IF EVERYTHING GOES
ACCORDING TO SCHEDULE,

06:24.520 --> 06:26.795
WE SHOULD BE AT THE MOTEL
IN BAKERSFIELD BY 1900.

06:26.900 --> 06:28.379
- I DON'T HAVE
MY FLAK JACKET.

06:28.490 --> 06:30.958
WE'RE GOING INTO A COMBAT ZONE?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:31.080 --> 06:33.219
[laughter]

06:33.320 --> 06:34.719
- DOES ANYBODY
HAVE TO PEE?

06:34.840 --> 06:36.284
- NO, SIR. NO, SIR.
- NO.

06:36.390 --> 06:37.800
- DO YOU HAVE TO PEE, JABBAR?
- NO, SIR.

06:37.910 --> 06:40.287
- SYDNEY, DO YOU HAVE TO PEE?
- NO, DO YOU?

06:40.400 --> 06:41.469
- ALL RIGHT,
IS EVERYBODY READY TO GO?

06:41.570 --> 06:42.662
LET'S ALL HAVE
A SAFE TRIP.

06:42.780 --> 06:46.534
HEY, OBEY THE SPEED LIMIT.
OBEY ALL TRAFFIC LAWS.

06:46.640 --> 06:48.631
I DON'T WANT ANYBODY BUSTED.
- OBEY THE SPEED LIMIT.

06:48.750 --> 06:50.149
- LET'S GET
ON THE ROAD NOW.

06:50.270 --> 06:53.023
[cheering]

06:53.130 --> 06:55.928
[horns honking]

06:56.030 --> 06:58.999
[Graffiti6's
Goodbye Geoffrey Drake]

07:04.070 --> 07:06.584
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

07:06.700 --> 07:09.453
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

07:09.560 --> 07:11.551
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

07:11.670 --> 07:14.002
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

07:14.120 --> 07:16.634
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

07:16.740 --> 07:18.947
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

07:19.050 --> 07:21.223
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:21.330 --> 07:23.605
FOREVER YOUNG

07:23.710 --> 07:26.292
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

07:26.410 --> 07:28.549
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

07:28.650 --> 07:31.301
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

07:31.410 --> 07:33.446
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

07:33.550 --> 07:36.269
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

07:36.380 --> 07:38.371
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

07:38.490 --> 07:40.344
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:40.460 --> 07:43.031
FOREVER YOUNG

07:43.150 --> 07:45.289
MAY YOU STAY

07:45.390 --> 07:48.598
FOREVER YOUNG

07:51.880 --> 07:53.393
[Graffiti6's
Goodbye Geoffrey Drake]

07:53.500 --> 07:56.628
- WE WERE BORN
IN SILENCE

07:56.750 --> 07:59.469
THERE'S NOTHING

07:59.580 --> 08:01.889
AND NO ONE
TO BLAME

08:06.650 --> 08:09.926
SOON WE LEARN
TO FIGHT

08:10.040 --> 08:13.168
OR DIE TRYING

08:13.280 --> 08:15.077
SO MY FATHER SAID

08:15.180 --> 08:17.978
YEAH RIGHT

08:18.080 --> 08:19.729
[cell phone chimes]

08:19.840 --> 08:22.422
'CAUSE ALL I WANTED
WAS A LITTLE LOVE

08:22.530 --> 08:23.974
AND TENDERN ESS
YEAH

08:24.080 --> 08:25.638
- WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU WANT TO STUDY, HADDIE?

08:25.740 --> 08:28.846
- UH, WHAT?
I DON'T KNOW, DAD.

08:28.950 --> 08:31.191
- COLLEGE.
- I DON'T KNOW.

08:31.300 --> 08:32.198
- YOU KNOW WHAT,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE

08:32.300 --> 08:34.814
THE TIME OF YOUR LIFE
IN COLLEGE, GUARANTEED.

08:34.920 --> 08:37.400
- [chuckles]
- WHO ARE YOU TEXTING?

08:37.510 --> 08:40.547
- CAROLINE.
- CAROLINE?

08:40.650 --> 08:41.787
SHE'S A SMART GIRL.

08:41.900 --> 08:44.653
DOES SHE KNOW WHERE SHE'S GOING
TO COLLEGE YET?

08:44.760 --> 08:47.308
- UH...[sighs]
UM, I DON'T KNOW.

08:47.420 --> 08:50.765
[phone chimes, Haddie giggles]

08:50.870 --> 08:52.758
- CHICKEN BONES,
ICE CREAM CONES

08:52.870 --> 08:54.838
THAT'S WHAT MAKES
THE WORLD GO ROUND

08:54.940 --> 08:56.737
LIZARD FEET,
TRICK OR TREAT

08:56.840 --> 08:58.899
THAT'S WHAT MAKES
THE WORLD GO ROUND

08:59.020 --> 09:00.806
TIPPY TOES

09:00.910 --> 09:02.605
THAT'S WHAT MAKES
THE WORLD GO ROUND

09:02.710 --> 09:04.598
HAPPY LEG
DA DA DA

09:04.710 --> 09:05.881
THAT'S WHAT MAKES
THE WORLD GO ROUND

09:05.990 --> 09:07.639
- OKAY! HEY, HEY.
GUYS, GUYS, GUYS.

09:07.750 --> 09:09.786
GUYS, OKAY,
WE'RE GONNA TAKE A LITTLE BREAK.

09:09.890 --> 09:10.857
JUST A LITTLE BREAK
FROM THE MUSIC.

09:10.960 --> 09:12.689
- YEAH.

09:12.790 --> 09:14.189
- I HAVE TO WRITE THIS BRIEF.
THANK YOU.

09:14.310 --> 09:15.789
- IT DOESN'T LOOK
