WITH KRISTINA.

14:48.020 --> 14:51.012
- WELL, YOU SHOULD BE
PUTTING YOUR FOOT DOWN.

14:51.130 --> 14:55.294
- WOULD YOU JUST STOP
AND GIVE ME A BREAK, OKAY?

14:55.410 --> 14:56.263
THIS IS MY FAMILY.

14:56.370 --> 14:57.473
I'M HAPPY TO BE HERE
FOR YOU,

14:57.580 --> 14:58.956
AND I AM SORRY
IF YOU'RE DISAPPOINTED,

14:59.070 --> 15:00.924
BUT KRISTINA HAD TO MAKE
A TOUGH DECISION WITH MAX,

15:01.030 --> 15:02.270
AND WE'RE GONNA STICK
WITH IT, ALL RIGHT?

15:02.380 --> 15:03.824
SETTLE DOWN.

15:03.930 --> 15:07.559
- I'M SETTLED.

15:07.660 --> 15:10.549
[door closes]

15:10.660 --> 15:11.934
- HE'LL BE FINE.

15:12.040 --> 15:14.281
HE'LL BE FINE
ONCE WE GET TO HIS MOM'S.

15:14.390 --> 15:18.178
YOU KNOW, IT'S JUST NOW HE'S GOT
THE--YOU KNOW, THE ANXIETY.

15:18.290 --> 15:19.518
- IS HE WORRIED ABOUT HER
'CAUSE SHE FELL?

15:19.640 --> 15:22.768
- NO, IT'S THE--IT'S
HIS WHOLE THING WITH HIS MOM.

15:22.880 --> 15:25.223
WELL, HE DIDN'T HAVE THE KIND
OF PARENTS THAT YOU KIDS HAVE.

15:25.330 --> 15:27.082
- SMOKING HOT?
- WHAT KIND IS THAT?

15:27.200 --> 15:28.337
- SMOKING HOT PARENTS?
- [laughs]

15:28.440 --> 15:30.328
- NO, SUPPORTIVE.

15:30.440 --> 15:32.499
WHEN HE WAS A YOUNG MAN,
HE HAD A LOT OF DREAMS.

15:32.620 --> 15:34.235
THERE WERE THINGS HE WANTED
TO DO AND BE AND--

15:34.340 --> 15:37.093
- LIKE WHAT?
- LIKE BEING AN ACTOR.

15:37.210 --> 15:38.689
- AWW.
- AND YOU KNOW WHAT SHE SAID

15:38.790 --> 15:41.179
TO HIM WHEN HE TOLD HER
HE WANTED TO BE AN ACTOR?

15:41.280 --> 15:42.656
- WHAT?

15:42.760 --> 15:45.172
- SHE SAID, "AND WHAT MAKES YOU
THINK YOU'RE SO SPECIAL?"

15:45.280 --> 15:47.077
AND HE WAS SPECIAL.

15:49.120 --> 15:52.283
BUT HE STILL HEARS HER VOICE
IN HIS HEAD, EVEN NOW.

15:52.390 --> 15:54.847
YOU KNOW, AND THE--I THINK,
IN SOME WAYS,

15:54.950 --> 15:57.464
HE STILL IS, UM,
SEEKING HER APPROVAL.

15:57.570 --> 16:01.529
- UH, WHOSE APPROVAL?
- THE W-WAITRESS'.

16:01.650 --> 16:04.164
- THE EXTRA SLAW.
- TALKING ABOUT MY MOM, HUH?

16:04.270 --> 16:05.817
- DAD, IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
WE WERE JUST TALKING ABOUT HOW

16:05.930 --> 16:07.124
MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T WORRY
SO MUCH

16:07.240 --> 16:08.639
ABOUT WHAT GRANDMA THINKS,
THAT'S ALL.

16:08.760 --> 16:10.068
- YEAH, WE DON'T WORRY
ABOUT WHAT YOU TWO THINK,

16:10.170 --> 16:11.273
AND LOOK AT US.

16:11.380 --> 16:12.347
WE'RE ALL, UH,
SMASHING SUCCESSES.

16:12.450 --> 16:14.179
- YEAH, CLEARLY.
- [chuckles]

16:14.280 --> 16:16.316
- BESIDES, GRANDMA'S, UH--
SHE'S A LITTLE BIT BONKERS.

16:16.420 --> 16:19.275
YOU SHOULDN'T LET HER OPINION
INFORM YOU ABOUT ANYTHING.

16:19.390 --> 16:20.971
- "BONKERS"?
I MEAN, SHE'S YOUR GRANDMA.

16:21.080 --> 16:22.149
HOW ABOUT A LITTLE RESPECT HERE,
CROSBY?

16:22.250 --> 16:23.285
- I THOUGHT I WAS BEING NICE
ABOUT IT.

16:23.390 --> 16:25.005
- JUST A LITTLE BIT.
JUST TONE IT DOWN A LITTLE.

16:25.120 --> 16:26.803
- IT'S CUTE.
IT'S LIKE A SITCOM.

16:26.910 --> 16:28.252
- IT ISN'T EVEN CHRIS--

16:28.360 --> 16:30.225
- IT'S BONKERS GRANDMA.
- GUYS--

16:30.330 --> 16:31.399
- THEN WHAT ARE YOU--

16:31.500 --> 16:34.253
